ifornia%20bill%20to%20regulate%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20bill%2C%20introduced%20by%20Sen.%20Scott%20Wiener%2C%20aims%20to%20deter%20unsafe%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAmendments%20include%20reduced%20penalties%2C%20clearer%20language%2C%20and%20increased%20reporting%20requirements.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheres-ai-company-amazon-betting-billions-on-anthropic-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20company%20Anthropic%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20now%20backing%20a%20controversial%20bill%20known%20as%20SB%201047%2C%20which%20would%20regulate%20AI%20in%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.sanity.io%2Ffiles%2F4zrzovbb%2Fwebsite%2F6a3b14a98a781a6b69b9a3c5b65da26a44ecddc6.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20sent%20to%20California%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%2C%20Anthropic's%20CEO%2C%20Dario%20Amodei%2C%20said%20the%20bill's%20%26quot%3Bbenefits%20likely%20outweigh%20the%20costs.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20he%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20are%20not%20certain%20of%20this%2C%20and%20there%20are%20still%20some%20aspects%20of%20the%20bill%20which%20seem%20concerning%20or%20ambiguous%20to%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnthropic's%20cautious%20approval%20comes%20just%20a%20month%20after%20the%20company%20proposed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-ai-bill-makes-openai-meta-google-anthropic-nervous-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseries%20of%20amendments%20to%20SB%201047%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20first%20introduced%20to%20the%20state%20legislature%20by%20Sen.%20Scott%20Wiener%20in%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20sent%20to%20state%20leaders%20in%20July%2C%20Anthropic%20called%20for%20a%20greater%20focus%20on%20deterring%20companies%20from%20building%20unsafe%20models%20rather%20than%20enforcing%20stringent%20laws%20before%20catastrophic%20incidents%20happen.%20It%20also%20suggested%20that%20companies%20be%20able%20to%20set%20their%20standards%20for%20safety%20testing%20instead%20of%20adhering%20to%20regulations%20prescribed%20by%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20amended%20version%20of%20the%20bill%20published%20on%20August%2019%20includes%20several%20modifications.%20First%2C%20it%20limits%20the%20scope%20of%20civil%20penalties%20for%20violations%20that%20don't%20result%20in%20harm%20or%20imminent%20risk%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsafesecureai.org%2Famendments%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Nathan%20Calvin%2C%20senior%20policy%20counsel%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20AI%20Safety%20Action%20Fund%2C%20which%20is%20a%20cosponsor%20of%20the%20bill%20and%20has%20been%20working%20with%20Anthropic%20since%20the%20bill%20was%20first%20introduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20some%20key%20language%20changes.%20Where%20the%20bill%20originally%20called%20for%20companies%20to%20demonstrate%20%26quot%3Breasonable%20assurance%26quot%3B%20against%20potential%20harms%2C%20it%20now%20calls%20for%20them%20to%20demonstrate%20%26quot%3Breasonable%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20%26quot%3Bhelps%20clarify%20the%20focus%20of%20the%20bill%20on%20testing%20and%20risk%20mitigation%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Calvin.%20It's%20also%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20common%20standard%20existing%20in%20tort%20liability%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20updated%20version%20also%20downsized%20a%20new%20government%20agency%20that%20would%20enforce%20AI%20regulations%2C%20once%20called%20the%20Frontier%20Model%20Division%2C%20to%20a%20board%20known%20as%20the%20Board%20of%20Frontier%20Models%20and%20placed%20it%20within%20the%20already%20existing%20Government%20Operations%20Agency.%20That%20board%20now%20has%20nine%20members%20instead%20of%20five%20members.%20With%20that%2C%20however%2C%20the%20reporting%20requirements%20on%20companies%20have%20also%20increased.%20Companies%20must%20publicly%20release%20safety%20reports%20and%20send%20unredacted%20versions%20to%20the%20state's%20attorney%20general.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20updated%20bill%20removes%20the%20penalty%20of%20perjury%2C%20thereby%20eliminating%20all%20criminal%20liability%20for%20companies%20and%20imposing%20only%20civil%20liabilities.%20Companies%20are%20now%20required%20to%20submit%20%26quot%3Bstatements%20of%20compliance%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20attorney%20general%20rather%20than%20%26quot%3Bcertifications%20of%20compliance%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20Frontier%20Model%20Division.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmodei%20said%20the%20bill%20now%20%26quot%3Bappears%20to%20us%20to%20be%20halfway%20between%20our%20suggested%20version%20and%20the%20original%20bill.%26quot%3B%20The%20benefits%20of%20developing%20publicly%20available%20safety%20and%20security%20protocols%2C%20mitigating%20downstream%20harms%2C%20and%20forcing%20companies%20to%20seriously%20question%20the%20risks%20of%20their%20technologies%20will%20%26quot%3Bmeaningfully%20improve%26quot%3B%20the%20industry's%20ability%20to%20combat%20threats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnthropic%20bills%20itself%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bsafety%20and%20research%20company%26quot%3B%20and%20has%20won%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-invests-4-billion-in-anthropic-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%244%20billion%20in%20backing%20from%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%202021%2C%20a%20group%20of%20former%20OpenAI%20staffers%2C%20including%20Dario%20Amodei%20and%20his%20sister%20Daniela%2C%20started%20the%20company%20because%20they%20believed%20AI%20would%20have%20a%20dramatic%20impact%20on%20the%20world%20and%20wanted%20to%20build%20a%20company%20that%20would%20ensure%20it%20was%20aligned%20with%20human%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWiener%20was%20%26quot%3Breally%20pleased%20to%20see%20the%20kind%20of%20detailed%20engagement%20that%20Anthropic%20brought%20in%20its%20'support%20if%20amended%20letter%2C%26quot%3B%20Calvin%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20really%20hope%20that%20this%20encourages%20other%20companies%20to%20also%20engage%20substantively%20and%20to%20try%20to%20approach%20some%20of%20this%20with%20nuance%20and%20realize%20that%20this%20kind%20of%20false%20trade-off%20between%20innovation%20and%20safety%20is%20not%20going%20to%20be%20in%20the%20long%20run%20interest%20of%20this%20industry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20companies%20that%20the%20new%20legislation%20will%20impact%20have%20been%20more%20hesitant.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-sam-altman-stance-california-ai-bill-regulation-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20sent%20a%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20week%20to%20California%20state%20leaders%20opposing%20the%20bill.%20One%20of%20its%20key%20concerns%20was%20that%20the%20new%20regulations%20would%20push%20AI%20companies%20out%20of%20California.%20Meta%20has%20also%20argued%20that%20the%20bill%20%26quot%3Bactively%20discourages%20the%20release%20of%20open-source%20AI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-position-california-ai-bill-sb-1047-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724530919000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ca32051aa2ac29ee33f9e1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-position-california-ai-bill-sb-1047-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Anthropic%20says%20the%20benefits%20of%20California's%20AI%20bill%20now%20%26quot%3Boutweigh%20its%20costs.%26quot%3B%20But%20it%20still%20has%20some%20concerns.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lvaranasi%40insider.com%20(Lakshmi%20Varanasi)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A41%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-position-california-ai-bill-sb-1047-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Let%E2%80%99s%20