rs'%3A%20Adults%20in%20their%20mid-50s%20who%20are%20woefully%20unprepared%20for%20retirement%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20empty%20savings%20jar%20with%20a%20label%20that%20says%20%26quot%3Bretirement%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661456d416bde8d4ead6bc2b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENearly%20half%20of%20Gen%20Xers%20think%20they%20will%20need%20to%20postpone%20retirement%2C%20a%20Prudential%20survey%20found.%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGen%20X%20may%20be%20even%20less%20prepared%20for%20retirement%20than%20boomers%2C%20wealth%20advisors%20say.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20large%20cohort%20of%20adults%20in%20their%20mid-50s%20have%20less%20than%20%2450%2C000%20in%20retirement%20savings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMany%20expect%20to%20work%20part-time%20or%20receive%20family%20help%20after%20retiring%2C%20a%20Prudential%20survey%20shows.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJim%20Thomas%2C%20a%2052-year-old%20who%20works%20in%20a%20lumber%20mill%2C%20is%20well%20aware%20of%20how%20far%20behind%20he's%20fallen%20in%20saving%20for%20retirement.%20His%20job%20pays%20%26quot%3Bgood%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20but%20he's%20still%20trying%20to%20plug%20the%20hole%20in%20his%20finances%20after%20a%20layoff%2C%20a%20divorce%2C%20and%20several%20legal%20disputes%20emptied%20his%20wallet%20in%20the%20last%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20expenses%20have%20dug%20a%20hole%20so%20deep%20in%20his%20savings%20that%20Thomas%20is%20only%20now%20starting%20up%20his%20401k%20from%20scratch.%20Currently%2C%20he%20estimates%20he%20has%20around%20%24100%2C000%20in%20savings%2C%20well%20below%20the%20goal%20that%20is%20traditionally%20recommended%20by%20financial%20advisors%2C%20who%20say%20you%20should%20have%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Faverage-401k-balance%23%3A~%3Atext%3DHow%2520much%2520you%2520should%2520save%2Cand%25208x%2520by%2520age%252060.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeight%20times%20your%20annual%20salary%20saved%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20time%20you're%2060.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20I%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20retire%20at%2065%20unless%20I%20win%20the%20lottery%2C%26quot%3B%20Thomas%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20expect%20that%20I%20will%20either%20need%20help%20from%20my%20daughter%20when%20I%20can%20no%20longer%20work%2C%20or%20I%20will%20need%20government%20assistance%20greater%20than%20Social%20Security.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20not%20alone.%20Thomas%20is%20among%20what%20retirement%20experts%20are%20calling%20%26quot%3Bsilver%20squatters%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20adults%20in%20their%20mid-50s%20who%20are%20even%20more%20woefully%20unprepared%20than%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-x-baby-boomers-savings-cant-afford-retirement-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboomers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20despite%20being%20about%20a%20decade%20away%20from%20retirement.%20%26quot%3BSquatters%26quot%3B%20refers%20to%20the%20possibility%20that%20many%20will%20have%20to%20rely%20on%20family%20for%20housing%20in%20later%20years.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20silver%20squatters%20go%2C%20Thomas's%20story%20is%20fairly%20common.%20According%20to%20surveys%20conducted%20by%20Prudential%20Financial%2C%20the%20median%20retirement%20savings%20for%20those%20in%20their%20mid-50s%20is%20just%20under%20%2448%2C000%2C%20with%2035%25%20of%2055-year-olds%20having%20less%20than%20%2410%2C000%20saved%20and%2018%25%20having%20saved%20nothing%20at%20all%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo-thirds%20of%2055-year-olds%20say%20they're%20afraid%20of%20outliving%20their%20savings.%20That's%20the%20highest%20level%20of%20fear%20among%20any%20age%20group%20of%20Prudential's%202024%20survey%2C%20with%2059%25%20of%2065-year-olds%20saying%20they%20worried%20they%20would%20outlive%20their%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20whole%2C%20they%20are%20not%20as%20prepared%20as%20the%20boomers%20and%20actually%20are%20doing%20less%20well%20than%20the%20millennials%2C%26quot%3B%20Pete%20Welch%2C%20managing%20director%20of%20retirement%20and%20wealth%20at%20Inspira%20Financial%2C%20told%20BI%2C%20though%20he%20noted%20that%20the%20youngest%20Gen%20Xers%20still%20had%20time%20to%20catch%20up%20on%20their%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20preparation%20among%20the%20cohort%20could%20be%20due%20to%20late%20planning%20and%20the%20unique%20economic%20circumstances%20of%20the%20mid-50s%20crowd%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20less%20financial%20literacy%20among%20the%20generation%2C%20wealth%20advisors%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERen%C3%A9%2C%20a%2050-year-old%20based%20in%20Austin%2C%20Texas%2C%20has%20anxiety%20over%20whether%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20will%20have%20enough%20to%20live%20comfortably%20once%20they%20retire.%20Their%20life%20savings%20%E2%80%94%20around%20%24380%2C000%20between%20the%20two%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20dwindled%20to%20next%20to%20nothing%20after%20a%20medical%20diagnosis%20put%20her%20out%20of%20work%20and%20through%20a%20string%20of%20surgeries%20over%20the%20course%20of%20two%20years%2C%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%2C%20who%20have%20fallen%20behind%20on%20some%20of%20their%20bills%2C%20don't%20know%20if%20they'll%20be%20able%20to%20get%20extra%20financial%20assistance%20once%20they%20retire%2C%20besides%20their%20expected%20pension%20payments.%20They%20have%20no%20external%20family%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20rely%20on%20their%20daughter%20for%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20like%2C%20oh%20God%2C%20how%20did%20we%20get%20here%3F%26quot%3B%20Ren%C3%A9%20said%2C%20describing%20a%20plea%20she%20made%20with%20their%20mortgage%20provider%20not%20to%20foreclose%20on%20their%20home.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20just%20going%20to%20have%20to%20work%20and%20401k-it%2C%20and%20that's%20just%20how%20it's%20going%20to%20have%20to%20be%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f121d0b8-9916-4ab0-ba06-3c3a4493d80f%5C%22%3EA%20forgotten%20generation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESilver%20squatters%20share%20some%20common%20characteristics%2C%20despite%20the%20unique%20circumstances%20affecting%20their%20retirement%20readiness.%20This%20group%20of%20Gen%20Xers%20%E2%80%94%20the%20generation%20of%20Americans%20aged%2043%20to%2059%20%E2%80%94%20largely%20expects%20to%20postpone%20or%20work%20past%20their%20retirement.%2047%25%20of%20Gen%20Xers%20think%20they'll%20have%20to%20retire%20later%20than%20they%20initially%20expected%2C%20while%2040%25%20expect%20to%20work%20part-time%20after%20they%20retire%2C%20per%20Prudential's%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20majority%20also%20don't%20expect%20to%20receive%20any%20inheritance%2C%20despite%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-not-waiting-pass-inheritance-wealth-transfer-millennials-need-it-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboomer%20predecessors%20holding%20onto%20trillions%20in%20wealth%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Only%2012%25%20of%20the%2055-year-old%20group%20expect%20to%20get%20money%20passed%20down%20from%20their%20family%20members%2C%20Prudential's%20survey%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20do%2C%20however%2C%20largely%20expect%20to%20be%20reliant%20on%20family%20for%20support%20once%20they%20retire.%20Around%2024%25%20of%2055-year-olds%20say%20they%20expect%20financial%20support%20from%20their%20family%20members%2C%20with%2021%25%20adding%20they%20also%20needing%20housing%20support%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20compares%20to%20just%2012%25%20of%2065-year-olds%20who%20say%20they%20will%20need%20that%20kind%20of%20help%20from%20family.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gap%20in%20retirement%20readiness%20could%20be%20due%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bunique%26quot%3B%20challenges%20of%20Gen%20Xers%2C%20according%20to%20Dylan%20Tyson%2C%20the%20head%20of%20retirement%20strategies%20at%20Prudential.%20He%20notes%20that%20all%20of%20the%20generation%20was%20in%20their%20prime%20working%20years%20during%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis%2C%20which%20could%20have%20set%20them%20back%20financially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Xers%20could%20also%20be%20in%20a%20tenuous%20stage%20of%20life%2C%20where%20a%20number%20of%20surprise%20expenses%20have%20popped%20up%20to%20drain%20their%20savings.%20Think%20of%20those%20who%20have%20had%20to%20fund%20their%20child's%20college%20education%20or%20are%20paying%20for%20a%20living%20facility%20for%20their%20own%20parents%2C%20Inspira's%20Welch%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20trying%20to%20help%20out%20here%2C%20you're%20trying%20to%20help%20out%20there%2C%20and%20then%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20there's%20just%20not%20enough%20on%20the%20table%20to%20really%20think%20about%20what%20you're%20going%20to%20do%20for%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20Welch%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20some%20of%20Inspira's%20Gen%20X%20clients%20had%20expressed%20frustration%20over%20their%20financial%20responsibilities%20to%20their%20family.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20just%20in%20a%20very%20tough%2C%20tough%20spot%20that%2C%20for%20whatever%20reason%2C%20I%20guess%20maybe%20the%20boomers%20didn't%20have%20to%20deal%20with.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELow%20rates%20of%20financial%20literacy%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20a%20widespread%20issue%20among%20every%20generation%20in%20the%20US%2C%20according%20to%20a%20study%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fagenda%2F2024%2F04%2Ffinancial-literacy-money-education%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Economic%20Forum%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20doesn't%20help%20the%20situation%2C%20Welch%20and%20Tyson%20say.%20Around%20half%20of%20Gen%20Xers%20are%20saving%20without%20a%20general%20plan%20for%20retirement%2C%20Prudential%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20also%20don't%20appear%20to%20be%20accounting%20for%20major%20expenses%20into%20retirement%2C%20with%2048%25%20not%20factoring%20in%20healthcare%20costs%20and%2075%25%20not%20factoring%20in%20assisted%20living%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20Prudential%20clients%20don't%20even%20know%20how%20much%20they%20need%20to%20save%2C%20Tyson%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20many%20of%20the%20firm's%20Gen%20X%20clients%20are%20simply%20guessing%20how%20long%20they%20will%20live.%20He%20said%20he%20believes%20many%20of%20them%20are%20guessing%20incorrectly%20due%20to%20rising%20life%20expectancies%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20have%20the%20cushion%20%E2%80%94%20again%2C%20this%20is%20the%20group%20we're%20talking%20about%2C%20the%2060-year-old%2C%20undersaved%20%E2%80%94%20they%20really%20need%20to%20be%20watching%20every%20penny%20and%20thinking%20about%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Welch%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-savings-crisis-gen-x-boomers-social-security-401k-pensions-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1724501762000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661456f41caec1275a6df1ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-savings-crisis-gen-x-boomers-social-security-401k-pensions-2024-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20large%20cohort%20of%20adults%20in%20their%20mid-50s%20is%20unprepared%20for%20retirement%20and%20may%20need%20to%20rely%20on%20family%20for%20housing%20and%20other%20needs%20later%20in%20life.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jsor%40businessinsider.com%20(Jennifer%20Sor)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A108%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-savings-crisis-gen-x-boomers-social-security-401k-pensions-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Former%20OpenAI%20employees%20call%20out%20Sam%20Altman%20for%2