tic%20development%20of%20the%20child%20and%20must%20take%20charge%20of%20their%20education.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDoing%20this%20would%20prevent%20these%20children%20from%20becoming%20adults%20who%20question%20their%20life%20choices%20at%2040%2C%20he%20states.%20What%20this%20boils%20down%20to%2C%20ultimately%2C%20is%20whether%20we%20feel%20happy%20in%20our%20lives.%20If%20the%20child%20sees%20a%20joyful%20adult%20who%20feels%20in%20control%20of%20their%20lives%2C%20they%20will%20learn%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20child%20is%20born%20to%20put%20in%20the%20effort.%20They%20learn%20to%20walk%20and%20talk%20by%20themselves.%20Why%20then%20do%20they%20become%20lazy%20by%20the%20time%20they%20are%2010%20years%20old%3F%20We%20must%20have%20done%20something%20wrong.%20Find%20a%20school%20which%20focuses%20on%20a%20child%2C%20not%20on%20creating%20engineers%20and%20doctors%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20need%20to%20ensure%20that%20our%20relationship%20with%20our%20partner%20is%20good%20as%20well%2C%20as%20that%20is%20your%20child%E2%80%99s%20definition%20of%20love.%20Ensure%20your%20relationship%20with%20work%20is%20great%20too%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Harpreet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20do%20we%20raise%20fearless%20children%20if%20we%20are%20fearful%20ourselves%2C%20he%20argues%3F%20This%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20you%20leave%20your%20child%20to%20do%20whatever%20they%20want.%20The%20idea%20is%20not%20to%20raise%20a%20consumer%2C%20but%20a%20person%20who%20has%20intrinsic%20motivation%20to%20do%20things.%20The%20best%20way%20to%20do%20that%20is%20by%20setting%20an%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20important%20for%20parents%20to%20walk%20the%20talk%2C%E2%80%9D%20agrees%20the%20school%20director.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20have%20any%20regrets.%20I%20intend%20to%20live%20my%20one%20life%20to%20the%20best%20of%20my%20ability%2C%20and%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20wish%